  h3 What about your uploaded media content?

  p
  | Castmill allows its users to upload any content to their accounts to be able
  | to stream said content to their screens or to share them with other
  | users.
  
  p
  | We treat your uploaded media more strictly than your personal information:
  | we do not sell, trade, take any commercial advantage, send the data to any
  | other third parties or use it in any other form unless given strictly permission
  | from the copyright holders of the content.
  
  p
  | In simpler words: we do not use your uploaded content for anything and we do not 
  | allow any other users or third parties to use it either.

  h3 How do we protect your uploaded media content?

  p
  | All data is transfered using an encrypted communication channel (at least TLS v1.1), and
  | is stored encrypted in Amazon's Simple Storage System using one of the bests industry standards, AES-256 
  | (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advanced_Encryption_Standard) encryption algorithm, 
  | which makes it virtual impossible for any outsider or any user of the system to access
  | the data. The data is only accessible in your account and by your screens since the
  | access URLs are cryptographically generated to be impossible to guess. Of course this 
  | does not apply if you choose to share your data to other users, as they will also 
  | be able to access the shared data depending on the rights that you choose to give them.

